</div></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Below is a week by week description of this course. It is based on the history of United States and aims to help students to understand the United States today while also improving language skills. </p>
<p>If this course is taught in hybrid format, then students will be doing every second week in on-demand format. </p>
<ol>
<li>Native Americans</li>
<li>The New World Meets the Old World</li>
<li>New Colonies and Slavery</li>
<li>American Revolution and a New Government</li>
<li>Early America: North, South, West and Slavery</li>
<li>The Civil War and Abraham Lincoln</li>
<li>Review 1: Units 1 - 6</li>
<li>Reconstruction, the West and Industrialization</li>
<li>Wealth, Labor and Imperialism</li>
<li>Early 20th Century to 1945</li>
<li>The Early Cold War</li>
<li>Civil Rights and the Vietnam War</li>
<li>The 1970s and the Middle East</li>
<li>The End of the Cold War and the 20th Century</li>
<li>Test</li>
</ol></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Quizzes and Assignments: 50%</p>
<p>Final Test: 50%</p>
<p>In the final test, students will be required to answer questions about content that they have learned in the course. </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><div class="OutlineElement Ltr  BCX0 SCXW36885951">
<p class="Paragraph SCXW36885951 BCX0"><span class="TextRun SCXW36885951 BCX0" lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" data-contrast="auto">The teacher of each course will explain the grading system in class. Based on a maximum score of 100, grades will be awarded as follows: S (Excellent) 90 - 100 A (Very good) 80-90 B (Good) 70-80 C (Pass) 60-70 D (Fail) Below 60.</span><span class="EOP SCXW36885951 BCX0" data-ccp-props="{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}"> </span></p>
</div>
